Crelay walks the dependency graph from a file to targets on which it
depends.  It uses the *.redep files created by credo, which store the
path and filename of targets which depend on the given file.

	> crean std

	> libdo (c cc c o) hello.o
	credo hello.o

	> libdo (c cc o '') hello
	credo hello

	> credo hello >[2=1] | sed 's,^,	,'
	credo   hello.dep
	credo     hello.o.dep
	credo   hello.o
	os -d /usr/inferno/github/credo/test/1/credo/hello cc -c hello.c
	credo hello
	os -d /usr/inferno/github/credo/test/1/credo/hello cc -o hello hello.o
	os -d /usr/inferno/github/credo/test/1/credo/hello ./hello

	> grep -n . *.redep | sed 's,^,	,'
	hello.c.redep:1: hello.o
	hello.o.redep:1: hello

